\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}=xI-V$
\end_inset

 for a scalar matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 then the largest invariant factor is the same as the minimal polynomial
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

.
